WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Hand washing should take you about one minute.

00:08.000 --> 00:13.000
Use a timer or count from 1 to 10 in each of the following steps.

00:13.000 --> 00:19.000
Wet hands with water and apply enough soap to cover all surfaces of the hands.

00:19.000 --> 00:23.000
Let the water run smoothly to avoid touching the tap later on.

00:23.000 --> 00:28.000
Rub hands palm to palm to obtain a good quantity of foam.

00:28.000 --> 00:35.000
Then rub right palm over the back of left hand with interlaced fingers and vice versa.

00:35.000 --> 00:40.000
Rub again palm to palm with fingers interlaced.

00:40.000 --> 00:44.000
Rub the back of your fingers to opposing palms with fingers interlocked,

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
repeating this action for each hand.

00:48.000 --> 00:55.000
Rub rotationally left thumb clasped in right palm and vice versa.

00:55.000 --> 00:59.000
To clean the tips of the fingers, rub rotationally backwards and forwards

00:59.000 --> 01:03.000
with clasped fingers of right hand in left palm and vice versa.

01:03.000 --> 01:09.000
Rinse hands thoroughly with running water.

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
Dry hands thoroughly with a single use towel.

01:13.000 --> 01:19.000
If the tap is not elbow operated, use this towel to turn off the tap without touching it directly.

01:19.000 --> 01:25.000
Your hands are now clean and safe.
